{{-- English: Data Protection Notice --}}
<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Savanna Hills Limited, trading as KiboAuto Marketplace and operating the website kiboauto.co.tz, is committed to respecting and protecting the privacy, confidentiality, integrity, and security of personal data collected through our website, digital platforms, communications, customer support channels, complaint channels, and all related services.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">This Data Protection Notice explains in detail how we collect, receive, record, organise, store, use, disclose, share, transfer, protect, retain, and otherwise process personal data relating to individuals who interact with KiboAuto Marketplace. This includes, without limitation, vehicle buyers, vehicle sellers, dealers, lenders, financing applicants, insurance applicants, persons submitting complaints, business partners, service providers, and general visitors to our website.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">We recognise that personal data must be handled lawfully, fairly, transparently, securely, and responsibly. For this reason, Savanna Hills Limited processes personal data in accordance with the laws of the United Republic of Tanzania, including the Personal Data Protection Act, 2022, together with any applicable regulations, guidelines, standards, or lawful directions issued by the Personal Data Protection Commission (PDPC). Savanna Hills Limited is registered with the PDPC in accordance with applicable legal requirements.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">This Notice is intended to help you understand: what personal data we collect; how and why we collect it; how we use it; when we may share it with third parties such as dealers, lenders, and service providers; how long we keep it; how we protect it; and what rights you may have in relation to your personal data.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">By accessing or using KiboAuto Marketplace, submitting information to us, creating an account, listing a vehicle, submitting a financing request, requesting connection to a dealer or lender, or using our complaint facilities, you acknowledge that your personal data may be processed in accordance with this Notice and applicable law.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. Who We Are</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">KiboAuto Marketplace is operated by Savanna Hills Limited, which is the entity responsible for determining the purposes and means of processing personal data collected through kiboauto.co.tz, except where this Notice states otherwise.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-2"><strong>Data Controller:</strong></p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-1 mb-3 ml-2">
        <li>Savanna Hills Limited</li>
        <li>Trading as: KiboAuto Marketplace</li>
        <li>Website: https://kiboauto.co.tz</li>
        <li><strong>Branch:</strong> Sinza Mori, Near Kitambaa Cheupe</li>
        <li><strong>Headquarters :</strong> Tan House, 9th Floor</li>
        <li>Email: info@kiboauto.co.tz</li>
        <li>Telephone: [Insert Telephone Number]</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">For the purposes of applicable data protection law, Savanna Hills Limited acts as the data controller in relation to personal data processed through KiboAuto Marketplace. In some situations, third parties such as dealers, lenders, insurers, payment processors, or professional advisers may process personal data as their own independent controllers; their own privacy notices may also apply.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">3. PDPC Registration</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Savanna Hills Limited confirms that it is registered with the Personal Data Protection Commission (PDPC) in accordance with the legal requirements applicable in Tanzania.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>PDPC Registration Number:</strong> [Insert PDPC Registration Number]</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Our registration with the PDPC reflects our commitment to lawful and accountable handling of personal data. We continue to implement internal controls, procedures, and safeguards designed to ensure that personal data is processed in a compliant, secure, and transparent manner.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">4. Scope of This Notice</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">This Data Protection Notice applies to all personal data processed by or on behalf of Savanna Hills Limited in connection with KiboAuto Marketplace, including personal data collected through the website, customer support channels, forms, email communications, account registration processes, marketing channels, complaint submissions, and interactions involving dealers, lenders, or other business partners.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-2">This Notice applies where you:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-1 ml-2">
        <li>visit, browse, or use kiboauto.co.tz;</li>
        <li>register for or maintain a user account;</li>
        <li>list, upload, promote, or advertise a vehicle;</li>
        <li>search for, compare, reserve, or inquire about a vehicle;</li>
        <li>request to be connected to a dealer, seller, or lender;</li>
        <li>submit financing-related information or request vehicle financing support;</li>
        <li>apply for or inquire about insurance-related services;</li>
        <li>submit a complaint through our complaints page or any other communication channel;</li>
        <li>communicate with our support team or representatives;</li>
        <li>subscribe to newsletters, promotional updates, alerts, or marketing communications;</li>
        <li>participate in surveys, promotions, competitions, campaigns, or feedback exercises; or</li>
        <li>otherwise interact with us in relation to our marketplace services.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-3">This Notice applies to personal data relating to natural persons. It does not necessarily apply to purely anonymous information that cannot reasonably identify an individual.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">5. Personal Data We Collect</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Depending on how you use our services, we may collect and process different categories of personal data.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5.1 Identity Data</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Full name; username or account name; date of birth (if collected); gender (if voluntarily provided); national identity details, including NIDA number, where required; profile photograph or image (if collected).</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5.2 Contact Data</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Mobile telephone number; email address; postal address; physical or residential address; region, district, or location details; preferred communication channel.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5.3 Account and Security Data</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Login credentials; password data in protected or encrypted form; one-time password (OTP) or verification data; account preferences; user settings; device/session authentication information; security logs and access records.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5.4 Vehicle and Listing Data</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Vehicle ownership information; vehicle registration details; engine number or chassis number; VIN or other identifying details; make, model, year, mileage, condition, and price; service history (if provided); valuation-related information; inspection details; photos, videos, descriptions, and listing content; inquiry and listing history.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5.5 Transaction and Service Data</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Reservation requests; lead details; transaction history; inquiry records; records of discussions with dealers, sellers, buyers, lenders, or support staff; service requests; support tickets; dispute records; records relating to financing, insurance, inspections, transportation, or logistics.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5.6 Complaint Data</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Where you submit a complaint through our complaints page at <a href="https://kiboauto.co.tz/cars/complaints" class="text-green-600 hover:underline">https://kiboauto.co.tz/cars/complaints</a> or through another channel, we may collect: your full name; contact details; details of the transaction or service giving rise to the complaint; complaint subject and description; supporting evidence or documents; communications relating to the complaint; internal handling notes; complaint outcome and resolution records.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5.7 Payment and Financial Data</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Payment reference details; billing information; records of fees paid or payable; payout details where required; refund-related information; finance application details; affordability or supporting financing details (where relevant); partial payment method details handled through secure third-party providers. We do not intend to store full payment card data unless handled securely through approved payment service arrangements.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5.8 Technical and Usage Data</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">IP address; browser type and version; device identifiers; operating system; language preferences; time zone; page views; searches; clicks; navigation patterns; referral sources; session information; cookies and similar identifiers; log and diagnostic data.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5.9 Marketing and Communication Data</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Newsletter subscription details; communication preferences; records of your consent; survey responses; campaign engagement history; records of marketing choices and opt-outs.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5.10 Verification, Compliance, and Risk Data</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Identity verification information; anti-fraud screening results; due diligence records; suspicious activity indicators; complaint and investigation records; legal correspondence; compliance-related files.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">6. How We Collect Personal Data</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-2">We collect personal data through several methods:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-1 ml-2">
        <li><strong>Directly from you</strong> – when you create an account, complete forms, upload a listing, contact us, request financing, submit a complaint, subscribe to updates, or communicate with us.</li>
        <li><strong>Automatically through technology</strong> – cookies, analytics tools, log files, and similar technologies when you use the website.</li>
        <li><strong>From third parties</strong> – dealers, sellers, lenders, insurers, payment processors, verification providers, service providers, public registers, or authorities where applicable.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">7. Why We Process Personal Data</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-2">We only process personal data where there is a lawful reason and a genuine business or legal need. Purposes include:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-1 ml-2">
        <li>To provide and operate the marketplace</li>
        <li>To connect clients with dealers and lenders</li>
        <li>To handle complaints and resolve disputes</li>
        <li>To verify identity and prevent fraud</li>
        <li>To facilitate related services (financing, insurance, inspection, etc.)</li>
        <li>To improve our services</li>
        <li>To communicate with users</li>
        <li>For marketing and business communications (where permitted or with consent)</li>
        <li>To comply with legal and regulatory requirements</li>
        <li>To protect rights and defend claims</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">8. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">Where applicable, we rely on one or more lawful bases, including: your consent; performance of a contract; steps at your request before entering into a contract; compliance with a legal obligation; protection of vital interests; legitimate interests (provided not overridden by your rights); or any other lawful basis under applicable law.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Where consent is relied upon, you may withdraw it at any time; withdrawal does not affect the lawfulness of processing carried out before withdrawal.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">9. Disclosure and Sharing of Personal Data</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">We share personal data only where there is a legitimate, lawful, necessary, and proportionate reason. We may share with: marketplace participants (buyers, sellers, dealers); dealers and lenders (where you request financing or contact); service providers and processors (hosting, payment, analytics, etc.); financing, insurance, inspection, and logistics partners; professional advisers; regulators and authorities (where required by law); and in the context of business transactions (merger, acquisition, etc.) subject to safeguards. We do not sell personal data as a separate commercial product.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">10. International Transfers</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Where personal data is transferred or accessed from outside Tanzania, we take reasonable steps to ensure it continues to receive an adequate level of protection through contractual commitments, access controls, security safeguards, and lawful transfer arrangements.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">11. Data Retention</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">We keep personal data only for as long as reasonably necessary for the purpose for which it was collected, or as required by law, dispute management, legal claims, security, auditing, or legitimate business operations. Retention periods vary by type of data (e.g. account data, complaint records, transaction records). When data is no longer needed, we take reasonable steps to securely delete, destroy, anonymise, or de-identify it.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">12. Data Security</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">We implement appropriate technical, administrative, and organisational measures to reduce the risk of accidental loss, misuse, unauthorised access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction of personal data. These may include: access restriction; password and authentication controls; encryption; role-based permissions; logging and monitoring; secure storage and hosting; confidentiality requirements; incident response procedures; and periodic review of security controls. No method of storage or transmission can be guaranteed completely secure; users should also protect their passwords, devices, and account credentials.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">13. Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">We use cookies and similar technologies to operate, secure, analyse, and improve our website and services (e.g. core functions, keeping users signed in, preferences, analytics, abuse prevention). You may manage cookies through your browser settings or cookie tools on the website; disabling certain cookies may affect your experience or limit some functions.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">14. Your Rights</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-2">Subject to applicable law, you may have rights including: to be informed about collection and use of your personal data; to request access to data we hold about you; to request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data; to request deletion, destruction, blocking, or anonymisation where appropriate; to object to certain processing; to withdraw consent where processing is consent-based; to request review of how your complaint or request has been handled; to lodge a complaint with us or the relevant authority; and to pursue other remedies under applicable law. These rights may be subject to exceptions, limitations, or procedural requirements.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">15. How to Exercise Your Rights</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">To exercise your rights, ask questions about how your data is handled, request access or correction, or raise a data protection concern, contact us using the details below.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-2"><strong>Privacy Contact</strong><br>Savanna Hills Limited / KiboAuto Marketplace<br>Email: [Insert Privacy Email]<br>Telephone: [Insert Telephone Number]<br>Address: [Insert Address]</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">We may request information to verify your identity before acting on a request, and may refuse, restrict, or defer a request where permitted or required by law.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">16. Complaints</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">If you have concerns about our services, marketplace conduct, transactions, or how your personal data has been handled, you may submit a complaint to us. You may use our complaints page at: <a href="https://kiboauto.co.tz/cars/complaints" class="text-green-600 hover:underline">https://kiboauto.co.tz/cars/complaints</a>. Provide enough information to enable us to understand, investigate, and resolve the matter fairly. We may process complaint information to review the issue, verify facts, communicate with the complainant, contact relevant parties, resolve disputes, and maintain records. If you are not satisfied with our response to a data protection concern, you may lodge a complaint with the PDPC in accordance with applicable law and procedures.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">17. Children's Data</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Our services are generally intended for adults. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children where such collection is not permitted by law or where appropriate safeguards are not in place. If you believe a child has submitted personal data to us improperly, please contact us so we can review and take appropriate steps.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">18. Third-Party Services and Links</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Our website may contain links to third-party services (dealer websites, lender portals, payment providers, etc.). Those third parties may process personal data under their own terms and privacy notices. Savanna Hills Limited is not responsible for the privacy practices, security, content, or operations of third-party services not under our control. Review their notices before sharing your information.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">19. Direct Marketing</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Where permitted by law, we may use personal data to send marketing communications (e.g. new listings, promotions, financing opportunities, service updates). You may opt out at any time via unsubscribe mechanisms, account settings, or by contacting us. We may still send non-promotional messages relating to your account, complaint, transaction, security, or legal matters.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">20. Automated Processing and Profiling</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">We may use limited automated systems for listing recommendations, search ranking, fraud detection, spam prevention, analytics, and user experience improvement. We do not intend to rely solely on automated decision-making producing legal or similarly significant effects unless lawful and with appropriate safeguards.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">21. Personal Data Breaches</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">In the event of a personal data breach or security incident, we will take appropriate steps to identify, investigate, contain, document, mitigate, and manage the issue. Where required by law or regulation, we may notify affected individuals, regulators, or other relevant bodies in accordance with applicable requirements and internal procedures.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">22. Changes to This Notice</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">We may update this Data Protection Notice from time to time to reflect changes in our services, operations, technology, legal requirements, regulatory expectations, or data processing practices. The latest version will be published on kiboauto.co.tz and will take effect from the date shown at the top. Users are encouraged to review this Notice periodically.</p>
</section>

